social_posts.post_text: 🍽️🧂🍷🌮 every time I scroll past these in my folder, they make me want a glass of wine and some tacos. I’m not even sure those two things pair well together but whatever. Photos from a summer shoot at @hop_haus

Last year I got to know more about @riverbendmalt via a partnership on their #riverbend10 ten years in the industry film. This year, I got a chance to meet the founders and tour the Malt house. It is a part of the process that as a consumer, is often forgotten about or not thought about at all. But I’ve become increasingly more curious about the process and the people involved throughout. It’s fascinating. And what makes Riverbend so wonderful is their commitment to locally sourced, local flavor, and their commitment to quality. It was such a privilege to see this side of the process. Thank you for your time Brian & Brent!

Small world. Love the beers and the fine folx at @waywardlanebrewing ⚡️

@newanthembeer was the place we visited while in Wilmington and pretty thrilled we had just enough time to visit before the wedding we were there to attend. It was azalea fest weekend which made getting around the city a bit difficult but fun nonetheless and worthwhile to fight the crowds to get here.

Richmond, VA || for the best smash burger of your recent lifetime, you head to @cobraburger 🍔 @barrelagedbeerd will attest to this fact. Two paper thin patty’s, bacon and that cheesy goodness paired with some salt and vinegar fries. 💥Chefs kiss 💥 Don’t miss it.

Pardon the shitty camera photo of the burger. 😐
We spent all weekend outside, hands in the dirt. It was exactly what I needed. Coupled with @allagashbrewing Wild Life Report it was a perfect weekend. 🌝🍃🪵

A vegetarian pepperoni pizza just for me. 😁😁 @triplecrossing is a favorite and the pizza was a bonus slice on top of the goodness that already exists there. Happy to have gotten back once again to drink a bunch of Bohem.  #richmondva #richmondcraftbeer

I’ve never been, maybe they weren’t open the last time we visited Richmond. So we checked out @bingobeerco while there and drank lagers while playing several rounds of skee-ball which ended in a draw for now… @barrelagedbeerd 🌝

Last years @finbackbrewery #whalewatching was one of the most epic times I’ve had at a beer fest leading to one epic summer. Sadly, I can’t make it this year and I’m devastated. But I want you to go so that you don’t sit behind your phone viewing the fun from afar like I must this time around. You’ll regret not showing up, it looks like the Finback gang is bringing the heat once again. ❤️‍🔥 #finbackwhalewatching #whalewatching2023

Ted’s door is just down that way. A little bit further and you’ve arrived at The Crown & Anchor (The Prince’s Head Pub). There’s a lively crowd gathered outside now, having a post work pint. Right around this time last year, I found myself in the mix. Many hadn’t yet heard of Ted Lasso, or didn’t care. Either way, I was gleeful to be walking this path, sitting down in that pub and taking it all in. I didn’t realize it until now, but I’m pretty sure I’m an Anglophile. 🇬🇧

Finback 🐋 NY [these look better in my story] 

11.8.23

I confidently order a beer, while internalizing the anxiety that I’m immediately going to hate it. Let’s try something new she thinks, and then, regret. Why did I order a full pour? 

That didn’t happen here, though this thought rushes over me every single time. 

All because of that one time I hated a beer so much that I sipped down a mouthful and made a beeline for the bathroom so as to not outwardly demonstrate I hated every inch of it by leaving an entirely full glass behind for the brewer to cleanup. 🙃🫠🫣 

Thankfully, on this evening, I sipped an excellent black lager from @threesbrewing while at @blindtigeralehouse last month!

Just read the news from @nickpalerm0 and I think you should go grab a beer with him before you have to drive a bit further to drink his beers…maybe? 😺 I love to see people growing and evolving, so happy for you pal! Here’s some photos I had the pleasure of taking of him a couple years ago now.
Someone once said, “It isn’t about avoiding the party,  it’s about being at the right one.” And I felt that.

A little something to celebrate the season with. Thank you for this delicious nitro milk stout @lefthandbrewing it poured so beautifully too. A little taste of Colorado right here in NY. Happy Festivus friends.
